# Piano Lesson Card Privacy Policy

Effective date: March 14, 2026

`Piano Lesson Card` (the "App") values your privacy and provides this Privacy Policy in compliance with applicable laws and regulations.

This document is based on the App's actual behavior as of March 14, 2026. The App currently operates without sign-up, login, server transmission, advertising, user tracking, or analytics features.

## 1. Personal Information We Collect

The App does not collect or transmit your personal information to the developer's server.

However, in order to provide core functionality, the following information that you enter may be stored only on your device:

- Date
- Practice piece/page
- Hand selection
- Memo
- Practice check status
- Save timestamp

This information is stored locally on your device solely to support the App's features and is not transmitted to the developer.

## 2. Purpose of Processing

The App processes the information you enter on your device only for the following purposes:

- Creating and temporarily saving practice cards
- Viewing previously saved practice cards
- Displaying practice progress

## 3. Retention and Deletion

The information you enter in the App is stored only on your device and may remain there until you delete it or remove the App.

Because the developer does not store this information on a separate server, the developer cannot directly access, modify, or delete your data.

You may remove locally stored information by:

- Deleting the App
- Using your device operating system's app data deletion feature
- Resetting to a new card within the App, where applicable

Please note that depending on your operating system or account settings, app data may be included in device backups such as iCloud or Google backups. Those backup areas are governed by the policies of the relevant platform provider.

## 4. Sharing with Third Parties

The App does not share your personal information with third parties.

## 5. Outsourced Processing

The App does not outsource the processing of your personal information to external service providers.

## 6. International Transfer

The App does not transmit your personal information to the developer's servers or external services. Therefore, the App itself does not cause any international transfer of personal information.

## 7. Cookies and Tracking Technologies

The App does not use cookies or similar tracking technologies.

The App also does not use advertising identifiers, behavioral tracking, or analytics tools.

## 8. App Permissions and Device Access

As of March 14, 2026, the App does not request access to contacts, location, camera, microphone, photos, health data, or other sensitive personal information permissions.

The App plays built-in audio assets to support learning-related functionality.

## 9. Children's Privacy

The App may be used by children as well as adults, but it does not collect personal information on the developer's servers.

Any information entered by the user is stored only on the device. Parents or guardians may remove the data by deleting the App or using device settings if needed.

## 10. Your Rights and Choices

You may manage the App data stored on your device yourself.

- You may choose not to enter information or to enter only minimal information.
- Stored information can be removed by deleting the App or using device settings.

Because the developer does not store personal information on a separate server, there is no server-side stored data that the developer can access, correct, or delete on your behalf.

## 11. Security Measures

The App is designed so that user information is not transmitted to external servers.

However, the level of protection may vary depending on your device security settings, lock screen protection, operating system security, and backup configuration. We recommend using a device passcode and keeping your operating system up to date.

## 12. Changes to This Privacy Policy

This Privacy Policy may be updated if the App's features, applicable laws, or operational policies change.

If there are significant changes, notice may be provided through app update information, the distribution page, or another appropriate notice method.

